article_title: As ObamaCare Continues To Struggle, Medicare Part D Keeps Shining

article_metadata.author: Doug Schoen

og.description: Yesterday, President Obama’s pick to be the next health secretary, Sylvia Mathews Burwell, faced questions over the troubled healthcare law. Burwell pledged to recoup any federal taxpayer dollars that were misused on failed health sign-up websites in states including Maryland and Oregon.
